    AbstractPortfolio
    Base class of portfolio classes AbstractPortfolio.executeConfiguration(CegarConfiguration, XCFA, long) is already implemented and can/should be used by subclasses AbstractPortfolio.executeAnalysis(hu.bme.mit.theta.xcfa.model.XCFA, java.time.Duration) is not implemented and should be the "main" method in the subclasses (concrete portfolios) Uses 2 threads when executing analysis Uses thread.stop() if analysis times out - use at your own risk
    CegarConfiguration
    This is a wrapper and extension to the XcfaConfig class It stores and is capable of returning the information an XcfaConfig stores, but it also stores information on the solvers used, if arg-cex check is used and if the solver is validated
